# Unratified — Marketing, User Journey, and UX Strategy

## Audience Architecture (Established 2026-03-02, expanded 2026-03-02)

### Three-Tier Advocacy Pipeline

The audience model operates across three tiers. The original three audiences (Hackers, Teachers, Scientists) function as **entry personas** — they describe how people discover and engage with the content. Two additional personas complete the advocacy pipeline: **Voters** (the conversion moment) and **Politicians** (the target of advocacy).

**Depolarization methodology**: Inspired by [Braver Angels](https://braverangels.org/) (formerly Better Angels), the conversion bridge frames ICESCR ratification as a nonpartisan issue using structured dialogue techniques (LAPP: Listen, Acknowledge, Pivot, Perspective). Economic rights cross partisan lines — conservatives value family stability and property rights; progressives value labor rights and social safety nets. The ICESCR protects both. See D015 in plan.md.decisions.

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                     ADVOCACY PIPELINE (3 TIERS)                      │
│                                                                      │
│  TIER 1 — ENTRY                                                      │
│  How people discover the site and engage with its content            │
│                                                                      │
│  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐   │
│  │  HACKERS         │  │  TEACHERS        │  │  SCIENTISTS      │   │
│  │  observatory.    │  │  unratified.org  │  │  observatory.    │   │
│  │  unratified.org  │  │  /educators      │  │  unratified.org  │   │
│  │  "Show me the    │  │  "Give me        │  │  "Show me the    │   │
│  │   analysis"      │  │   materials"     │  │   methodology"   │   │
│  └────────┬─────────┘  └────────┬─────────┘  └────────┬─────────┘   │
│           │                     │                      │             │
│           └─────────────────────┼──────────────────────┘             │
│                                 ▼                                     │
│  TIER 2 — CONVERSION                                                 │
│  The moment an informed person decides to act                        │
│                                                                      │
│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │
│  │  VOTERS                                                      │    │
│  │  unratified.org/action                                       │    │
│  │  "I understand — now what do I DO?"                          │    │
│  │                                                              │    │
│  │  Not a demographic. A functional role. Anyone in any entry   │    │
│  │  persona becomes a Voter when they decide to act. A hacker   │    │
│  │  who contacts their senator occupies both Hacker and Voter   │    │
│  │  personas simultaneously.                                    │    │
│  └──────────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘    │
│                                 │                                     │
│                          constituent                                 │
│                          pressure                                    │
│                                 ▼                                     │
│  TIER 3 — TARGET                                                     │
│  Who receives the advocacy and makes the political calculation       │
│                                                                      │
│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │
│  │  POLITICIANS (via legislative staff)                          │    │
│  │  unratified.org/action/policy-brief                          │    │
│  │  "What would I vote for, and can I survive voting for it?"   │    │
│  │                                                              │    │
│  │  The site addresses politicians indirectly, through voter    │    │
│  │  pressure. The functional persona: the legislative aide who  │    │
│  │  evaluates the site and decides whether to brief the senator.│    │
│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │
│                                                                      │
│  SUPPLY CHAIN:                                                       │
│  • Entry personas: evaluate + amplify + validate (content power)     │
│  • Voter persona: convert understanding into constituent pressure    │
│  • Politician persona: target of pressure, holds legislative power   │
│  • Commercial Publishers (Aud 4): scale delivery channel (future)    │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Why NOT a general public audience

The general public arrives through one of the three entry channels, not independently. Attempting to serve "everyone" dilutes content for the audiences who actually engage with it. General public reach arrives as a second-order effect: teachers bring it to students, HN amplifies it to the broader tech community, academic citations bring it to policy circles.

The **Voter** persona does not contradict this. Voter describes a *functional role*, not an entry channel. Every entry persona feeds into the voter conversion moment. "Voter" answers the question: *what happens after someone finishes reading?*

