## External Review: Fair Witness Positive Psychology Strategy (2026-03-04)

An external agent produced a "Dignity-Trust Nexus" marketing strategy. Fair witness assessment:

**Validated**: The strategy correctly identifies fair witness principles, dignity-centered design, methodology transparency, bipartisan framing, and educational primacy as core values. All already implemented (D004, D015, D017, D029, D038).

**Conflicts resolved — existing decisions hold**:
1. "Positive psychology strengths-based framing" conflicts with prohibition framing (D029). *"No person should lack healthcare"* carries more advocacy urgency than *"The U.S. has strong healthcare foundations."* Fair witness reports the gap. Prohibition framing stands.
2. "Behavioral influence disclosure" implies we use behavioral influence techniques. We do not. No action needed.

**Extracted**: Success metrics vocabulary (see section above). Educational partnership initiatives concept (aligns with deferred educator outreach).

**Deferred as out of scope**: Monthly/quarterly/annual audit cadence, bias detection systems, community oversight mechanisms — organizational overhead exceeding current project scale.

**Observatory positioning note**: Extracted as standalone section below.

