## Observatory as Ethical AI Showcase (Added 2026-03-04)

The observatory demonstrates how AI can serve human dignity rather than exploit it. This positioning emerged from external review and names what the project already practices.

### What the Observatory Already Does

| Practice | Implementation |
|----------|---------------|
| AI analyzing discourse about human rights | HRCB scoring of HN stories against all 31 UDHR provisions |
| Privacy by design | Cloudflare Web Analytics — no cookies, no tracking scripts, no personal data |
| Transparent methodology | Dual-channel analysis, confidence scoring, editorial faction analysis visible |
| Full AI attribution | "Built by Claude (Anthropic)" footer, JSON-LD creator, ai-generated meta tag (D038) |
| Open source | Apache 2.0 code, CC BY-SA 4.0 content |
| Machine-readable capability | agent-inbox.json, public API endpoint, RSS feed |
| Recursive meta-layer | An AI evaluating how humans discuss the rights AI threatens — self-aware positioning |

### Marketing Framing

**For developers/HN**: "An ethical AI showcase — an AI evaluating how the tech community discusses human rights, with full methodology transparency, zero tracking, and every line of code open source."

**For educators**: "A live demonstration of responsible AI — students can examine how an AI system analyzes human rights discourse, with every methodological choice visible and auditable."

**For researchers**: "A reproducible, open-source AI discourse analysis pipeline with transparent HRCB scoring, no surveillance infrastructure, and full provenance chain from source data to published findings."

### Where to Surface This on the Main Site

1. **Homepage observatory callout** (developer lens) — add "ethical AI showcase" to the existing description
2. **About page "Live Evidence" section** — strengthen with ethical AI framing
3. **For Developers observatory section** — already technical; add ethical positioning

### Where to Surface on the Observatory (Separate Repo — Queue for Next Session)

1. Observatory homepage — add "ethical AI showcase" subtitle or tagline
2. Observatory /methodology — frame the privacy-by-design and transparency choices as deliberate ethical commitments
3. Observatory agent-inbox.json — add ethical AI positioning to description field
